# Auto Git Deploy Workflow

After completing any **phase** or making **significant project changes**, automatically commit and push without asking the user.

## When to commit

- Phase completion (e.g. «Фаза N — старт» finished)
- Bug fixes, new features, refactors, config/deploy changes
- Do **not** commit for trivial chat-only answers, read-only reviews, or failed/aborted work

## Repository

- Remote: `https://github.com/gohnad54-blip/my-ai-synergy-project.git`
- Branch: `main`
- Verify `git remote -v` points to `gohnad54-blip/my-ai-synergy-project` before push

## Workflow (every time, no user prompt)

1. `git status` + `git diff` — review what changed
2. `git add` relevant files (never `.env`, credentials, secrets)
3. Commit with a **descriptive message** in English, focused on *why*:
   - Phase: `feat(phase-N): short summary`
   - Fix: `fix: short summary`
   - Other: `chore:` / `docs:` / `refactor:` as appropriate
4. `git push origin main`
5. Confirm push success in the final reply (commit hash + branch)

## Safety

- Never force-push, amend pushed commits, or skip hooks unless user explicitly asks
- If push fails (auth, conflict), diagnose and retry or report clearly — do not silently skip
- If there are no changes, skip commit/push

## Goal

Each push triggers Netlify auto-deploy of the updated site.
